01:35:33.234 --> 01:35:35.054
Recess, back to one!

01:35:35.557 --> 01:35:37.286
— Alright, recess.
— We going again!

01:35:37.659 --> 01:35:40.611
Again, everyone!
And… we’re rolling!

01:35:40.641 --> 01:35:43.460
— We’re going to the producer’s building.
— Sorry, we’re rolling

01:36:19.355 --> 01:36:22.161
Sorry pal, we’re gonna be in the movie.
Call my agency.

01:36:22.196 --> 01:36:23.712
Sir!

01:36:35.814 --> 01:36:38.284
Studio 6 Productions.

01:36:38.390 --> 01:36:40.896
May I speak to a Mr. Kevin Harkins?

01:36:41.027 --> 01:36:44.310
I’m sorry, Mr. Harkins is out of
country on a location scout.

01:36:44.318 --> 01:36:46.079
May I take a message?

01:37:02.803 --> 01:37:06.317
Doors are closing for
flight 3‒6‒3 to Zurich.

01:37:15.004 --> 01:37:17.107
— We can go.
— Excellent.

01:37:24.753 --> 01:37:28.089
You can these. It’s a gift.

01:37:40.461 --> 01:37:43.269
[Farsi] Wait a moment.
Others are coming.

01:39:59.769 --> 01:40:03.225
Swissair 3‒6‒3, clearance for taxi.

01:40:05.145 --> 01:40:09.680
Swissair 3‒6‒3, you are
number two for departure.

01:40:57.620 --> 01:41:00.854
Swissair 3‒6‒3, you are
cleared for take off.

01:41:04.402 --> 01:41:07.047
Swissair 3‒6‒3,
clear for take off.

01:42:11.998 --> 01:42:15.346
— We got wheels up!
— Wait.

01:42:29.994 --> 01:42:32.313
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is our pleasure to announce

01:42:32.324 --> 01:42:34.394
that alcoholic beverages
are now available

01:42:34.397 --> 01:42:37.009
as we have cleared Iranian airspace.

01:43:25.228 --> 01:43:26.598
They’re clear.

01:43:27.318 --> 01:43:29.265
Yes! Yes!

01:43:33.762 --> 01:43:35.350
They’re out!

01:43:35.973 --> 01:43:37.740
They’re out. They’re out!

01:43:37.756 --> 01:43:39.576
Yes! We got them out!

01:43:42.205 --> 01:43:43.916
They’re out!

01:43:49.822 --> 01:43:51.989
Great work, boys.

01:43:52.077 --> 01:43:53.748
We’ve managed!

01:44:04.238 --> 01:44:07.546
You are admitted to the republic of Iraq.

01:44:52.767 --> 01:44:54.876
We made history today.

01:44:55.709 --> 01:44:59.151
“ History starts out as farce
and ends up as tragedy‟.

01:44:59.595 --> 01:45:01.492
Or it’s the other way around.

01:45:01.752 --> 01:45:02.956
And who said it?

01:45:03.122 --> 01:45:04.575
Marx.

01:45:05.285 --> 01:45:08.390
Groucho said that?

01:45:10.902 --> 01:45:13.884
Called ‘The Times’ to nail
it to the Goddamn door.

01:45:13.927 --> 01:45:15.285
CIA are the good guys.

01:45:15.297 --> 01:45:17.193
The Canadians are the good guys

01:45:17.497 --> 01:45:19.749
And if we’re not agreeing, them too.

01:45:19.791 --> 01:45:24.146
Only. Canada takes the credit, or
they’ll retaliate against the hostages.

01:45:25.201 --> 01:45:27.097
Great Satan wasn’t involved.

01:45:27.872 --> 01:45:29.923
No CIA.

01:45:30.014 --> 01:45:32.040
Is that right, Jack?

01:45:33.807 --> 01:45:35.718
Involved in what?

01:45:36.385 --> 01:45:39.595
We were surprised as anybody.

01:45:41.836 --> 01:45:43.695
Thank you, Canada.

01:45:43.837 --> 01:45:46.366
We knew that each day
that they stayed there,

01:45:46.367 --> 01:45:48.706
the danger was becoming greater.

01:45:48.802 --> 01:45:52.752
We had been looking for a solution to have
them to leave the country during the past—

01:45:52.779 --> 01:45:56.157
.. Day 87, and finally a sliver
of really good news…

01:45:56.229 --> 01:45:58.716
.. American department of State
hereby honors

01:45:59.315 --> 01:46:00.971
Joe Stafford…

01:46:01.580 --> 01:46:02.987
Kathy Stafford…

01:46:04.518 --> 01:46:06.119
Mark Lijek…

01:46:07.049 --> 01:46:09.857
The Americans will be forever grateful

01:46:09.910 --> 01:46:12.098
to our great and ally to the North,

01:46:12.110 --> 01:46:14.734
for the protection and safe passage,

01:46:14.832 --> 01:46:16.520
provided to our diplomats.

01:46:16.632 --> 01:46:17.886
Bob Anders…

01:46:18.276 --> 01:46:20.693
Here or anywhere in the world…

01:46:20.789 --> 01:46:22.661
Canada will pay…

01:46:24.060 --> 01:46:27.924
for this violation of the
sovereignty of Iran.

01:46:28.049 --> 01:46:32.578
.. ambassador Ken Taylor
and the great nation of Canada.

01:46:36.325 --> 01:46:38.589
So I’m sitting in Jerry’s this morning,

01:46:38.708 --> 01:46:40.343
I’m having breakfast.
Waitress comes over to me,

01:46:40.411 --> 01:46:42.216
she’s waving a newspaper, she says:

01:46:42.266 --> 01:46:44.054
“You see what those Canadians pulled off?

01:46:44.190 --> 01:46:46.300
Why can’t we do something like that?‟

01:46:46.429 --> 01:46:48.624
I said to her, do you know what I said?

01:46:48.807 --> 01:46:50.206
No, what?

01:46:50.362 --> 01:46:52.994
“Argo, fuck yourself!‟

01:47:20.964 --> 01:47:22.485
All set.

01:47:22.803 --> 01:47:24.623
Thanks a lot.

01:47:38.583 --> 01:47:41.344
And I left my autograph book at home.

01:47:46.629 --> 01:47:49.964
His eminence called me.
He wants to see you.

01:47:50.221 --> 01:47:52.751
Probably wants to fire me himself.

01:47:53.127 --> 01:47:56.319
He wants to give you
the Intelligence Star.

01:47:56.601 --> 01:47:58.432
You’re getting the highest award of merit

01:47:58.435 --> 01:48:02.115
of the clandestine services
of these United States.

01:48:02.925 --> 01:48:04.847
Ceremony’s on the fourteenth.

01:48:05.190 --> 01:48:08.949
If they push it a week I can bring
Ian, that’s his winter break.

01:48:09.839 --> 01:48:14.043
The op was classified. So…
the ceremony’s classified.

01:48:14.129 --> 01:48:17.761
He can’t know about it,
nobody can know about it.

01:48:18.892 --> 01:48:22.739
So they’re just gonna give me an award,
then they’re gonna take it back.

01:48:22.812 --> 01:48:24.549
That’s right.

01:48:25.489 --> 01:48:28.930
If we wanted applause we would
would have joined the circus.

01:48:29.112 --> 01:48:31.806
— I thought we did.
— Yeah.

01:48:32.018 --> 01:48:35.421
Carter said you were a great American.

01:48:35.798 --> 01:48:37.383
Great American what?

01:48:37.980 --> 01:48:39.803
He didn’t say.

01:48:52.746 --> 01:48:55.469
What happened to your picture?

01:48:55.704 --> 01:48:57.985
It’s in turn around.

01:49:38.931 --> 01:49:41.311
Can I come in?

01:50:25.425 --> 01:50:27.667
The Iran hostage crisis
ended on January 20, 1981,

01:50:27.969 --> 01:50:30.526
when all remaining
hostages were released.

01:50:31.327 --> 01:50:34.871
They spent 444 days in captivity.

01:50:35.369 --> 01:50:38.478
The involvement of the C.I.A. complemented
efforts of the Canadian embassy

01:50:38.804 --> 01:50:41.803
in freeing the six held in Tehran.

01:50:43.128 --> 01:50:45.808
To this day, this story stands
as an enduring model

01:50:46.040 --> 01:50:49.601
for international cooperation
between governments.

01:50:50.324 --> 01:50:53.050
All of the Houseguests returned to U.S.
foreign service

01:50:53.216 --> 01:50:55.926
after their ordeal in Iran.

01:50:57.287 --> 01:50:59.991
Oscar winning make-up artist
John Chambers was awarded

01:51:00.248 --> 01:51:02.896
the C.I.A.’s Intelligence medal,
its highest civilian honor.

01:51:03.507 --> 01:51:06.510
He and Mendez remained friends
until Chamber’s death in 2001.

01:51:07.235 --> 01:51:10.036
Tony Mendez’s Intelligence Star
was returned to him in 1997,

01:51:10.299 --> 01:51:13.799
when operation Argo was declassified
by president Clinton.

01:51:22.641 --> 01:51:26.180
He lives in rural Maryland
with his family.

